  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "translator-2",
    "senderColor": "yellow",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Replace \"equally\" with \"also\" — 也同样 means extension, not parity",
    "content": "The original Chinese is: \"现象礼不仅仅存在于在我对待他人时，**也同样**存在于其他人是如何对待他人上\"\n\n也同样 = \"also similarly\" / \"also in the same way.\" It asserts that phenomenal ritual conduct exists in both places in the same manner -- my treatment of others AND others' treatment of one another.\n\n\"Equally\" is a reasonable rendering of 也同样 but it subtly overstates. \"Equally\" in English implies an exact balance or parity between the two cases. The Chinese 也同样 is softer -- it says \"also, in the same way\" without asserting precise equality. The emphasis is on *extension* (it exists there too), not on *degree* (it exists there to the same extent).\n\nRecommendation: replace \"equally\" with \"also\" --\n\n\"Phenomenal ritual conduct exists not only in how I treat others, but also in how other people treat one another.\"\n\nThis matches the 也同样 -- assertive extension without a claim about degree."
  }
}
